  "title": "Bush Whack",
  "description": "Ever wondered how to perform the “Assisted Pee Over Water”? Join storyteller Holly M. Brinkman on this coming-of-age adventure. You’ll laugh. You’ll cry. You’ll try not to pee your pants. “We all need a Pee Buddy, and... should be a Pee Buddy to others.” ★★★★ Montreal Theatre Hub. \"Too good to hold in.\" ★★★★★ Victoria Showbill",
  "credits": "<strong>Playwright</strong>: Holly Maryan Brinkman<br/><strong>Director</strong>: Holly Maryan Brinkman<br/><strong>Cast</strong>: Holly Brinkman<br/><strong>Stage Manager</strong>: Stephanie Taylor<br/>",
  "website": "https://www.instagram.com/hollymaryan",
  "plain_language": "Bush Whack is a one-woman show about Holly Brinkman's life growing up in British Columbia. She is from a small town and in her childhood spends a lot of time outside. She likes to pee outside and has lots of funny suggestions of different ways for you to be able to do that to! As she gets older she has some hard experiences and will tell you about them. A funny show that is also very emotional.",
